Organisation Name: High Peak Borough Council & Staffordshire Moorlands District Council
Title: HPBC Leisure Centres Management & Operating Contract
Description:
High Peak Borough Council wish to appoint a suitably experienced and competent Leisure operator to deliver leisure services and activities at the Council's Leisure sites to the local and extended communities. We are inviting proposals through an Open tender procedure compliant under Section 7 of the Public Contracts Regulations 2015, to secure a five year contract for this service.

In addition to the operation of the Leisure centres, there will be a requirement for the operator to lead on capital works projects at the various sites and some grounds maintenance responsibilities at extended recreational sites.

The Council owns four Leisure sites across High Peak;

• Buxton Swimming & Fitness Centre , St John's Road, Buxton, SK17 6BE

• Glossop Leisure Centre, High Street East, Glossop, SK13 8PN

• Glossop Swimming Pool, Dinting Road, Glossop, SK13 7DS

• New Mills Leisure Centre, Hyde Bank Road, New Mills, High Peak, SK22 4BP

The Facilities across the locations, host a mixture of activities and fixed equipment including for example;  Sports Hall multi-use, Swimming pools, Fitness Suites, Dance Studios, Squash Courts, outdoor hard Courts, Athletics and Cycle Track and Grass pitches.

This exercise is being managed through the Council's Electronic tendering system Procontract. To Register an Interest and submit a tender for this opportunity please click on the link below:

Project reference number: DN359530

https://supplystokeandstaffs.proactishosting.com

You will need to register or log in (if you have already registered). If you have any queries or need assistance please contact us:

Email:  procurement@highpeak.gov.uk

Reference: P3734

Closing date and time: Wednesday 31st October 2018 by 12:00 noon

Title: Design, Build, Operate and Maintain (DBOM) Contract for North Devon District Council Leisure Facilities
Description:
The contract includes the design and build of a new leisure centre, located in Barnstaple, which will form anextension to the current Tarka Tennis Centre. It will also include the management and operation of the following facilities:
• Existing Tarka Tennis Centre including the new build leisure centre referred to above.
• New build full-size Artificial Grass Pitch (3G) subject to delivery by NDDC.
• Ilfracombe Pool & Fitness Centre                                                                                                                                                                                                          
Design & Build anticipated to run from 8 November 2019 to opening.                                                                                                                                                    This is a Design, Build, Operate & Maintain contract.                              
The design and build part of the contract is valued at £13,808,712.  
The operate and maintain part of the contract will involve the management of the leisure facilities at the Contractor's risk but will include an Annual Payment, from  the Contractor to the Authority, of £380,517.
Operate & Maintain to run 20 years from commencement of the Service Period anticipated to be 18 October 2021.

Title: Concession Contract:  P3363 Provision of Hospitality, Catering and Events at the Pavilion Gardens Buxton
Description:
High Peak Borough Council wish to invite proposals from suitable operators in the Catering, Hospitality and Leisure industry to provide Hospitality, Catering and Events Services under the form of a Concession Contract for the Pavilion Gardens Visitor attraction situated in Buxton Derbyshire.

The Pavilion Gardens is an excellent historic venue situated in the heart of the spa town, providing a visitor attraction popular for catering and events to the local community, visitors and tourists to the town. The Council is looking to appoint a successfully established and experienced organisation to deliver and promote a high quality, value for money experience for visitors.

This exercise is being completed in accordance with the Concession Contract Regulations 2016 as advertised in the Official Journal of the European Union.
The intended start date for this contract is 1st January 2019.

This exercise is being managed through the Council's Electronic tendering system Proactis. To Register an Interest and submit a tender for this opportunity please visit the website below and select opportunities, Project reference number DN331466
https://supplystokeandstaffs.proactishosting.com/

You will need to register or log in (if you have already registered). The site is free to register and use and you will be given a secure login by the portal providers.

Requests to express an interest in this opportunity will be approved by the Council, prior to prospective participants accessing the full ITT (Invitation to Tender) Information.
If you have any queries or need assistance please contact us on procurement@highpeak.gov.uk or phone 0345 129 77 77

Title: Tender for the provision of Mechanical and Electrical (M&E) Planned preventative and responsive maintenance
Description:
Erewash Borough Council has a requirement for a range of Mechanical and Electrical (M&E) planned preventative and responsive maintenance services.  Tenders are therefore being sought for the provision of these services.  

The tender has been split into 5 lots:

Lot 1 - Air conditioning and ventilation fans (circa £2,200 per annum)
Lot 2 - Automatic doors and roller shutters (circa £4,000 per annum)
Lot 3 - Emergency lighting and reactive electrical maintenance (circa £15,000 per annum)
Lot 4 - Gas/associated equipment and reactive mechanical maintenance (circa £14,200 per annum)
Lot 5 - Lightning protection and chimneys (circa £4,200 per annum)

Tenderers can bid for an individual or combination of lots however, a maximum of 3 lots can be bid for. 

Please note, in February 2019, the Council outsourced the management of its leisure centres and services to Parkwood Leisure Ltd.  Therefore, the scope of this tender does not include services at any leisure sites.
